newsitem.title: SINGAPORE: Singapore gas oil trades at $25.20/bbl.
newsitem.headline: Singapore gas oil trades at $25.20/bbl.

text.p: Gas oil traded in the Singapore cash market on Thursday at $25.20 per barrel, down $5.45 from the last deal done on January 10 at $30.65, traders said.
The cargo, sold by local trader Sanko Oil to Dutch trader Vitol, is for 190,000-barrel loading February 15-19 on a free-on-board Singapore basis.
The sale represents an 18 percent fall from the previous deal.
Gas oil prices have collapsed to a five-month low after Chinese buyers withdrew from the market leading to an over supply of prompt cargoes.
